RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 30000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000, if for $45,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BATI KING was sent clear from the inside, held a clear lead inside the eighth pole while racing nearing the inside and prevailed late under strong handling. COPPER TAX chased the top pair early on, raced two to three deep in the stretch run, surged late and just missed in a game effort. PRINCE FRED was coaxed along from the inside and had not enough for the top pair. DUBLSHOTOFCOURAGE dropped near the back of the pack early, raced four to five wide into the upper stretch and never was a factor. WESLEY THOMAS chased the early pace between rivlas and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Dublshotofcourage
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, 4-5 wide upper stretch, no factor

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 14000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE DECEMBER 10, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 10, 2023 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since March 10, 2023 Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BREITHORN dueled from the inside of foes early on, dug in near the eighth pole and proved best under strong handling. TACO BEAN dueled for the early lead from the outside of foes and finished gamely to the wire. UNDERDOG dueled for the early lead between rivals and kept on to the wire. CLASSY SOLUTION chased the early pace, lacked racing room near the three eighths pole, was four deep past the quarter pole and kept on willingly to the wire. Jockey of Classy Solution claimed objection for interference on Breithorn and stewards ruled no change. KIRBY raced far back and never threatened.

ENTRY.NAME: Underdog
ENTRY.OWNER: Bone Robert D and Wayward Farm
